  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="synthesis-actividad-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[@@@@@@@@@] At the conclusion of the previous lesson, students should have seen that we can approach solving any equation of the form <m>px = q</m> (where <m>p</m> and <m>q</m> are rational numbers and <m>x</m> is unknown) by dividing each side by <m>p</m>. Also, we can approach solving any equation of the form <m>x + p = q</m> by subtracting <m>p</m> from each side. Discussion should focus on given <m>\num{0.07} = 10m</m>, we can write <m>\num{0.07} \div 10 = 10m \div 10</m> and then <m>\num{0.007} = m</m>.</p>
